      "id": "bug-031",
      "timestamp": "2026-06-01T13:00:00.000Z",
      "error_message": "OBS log (Windows/D3D11): 'device_vertexbuffer_create (D3D11): Invalid texture vertex size specified' — mask quad never drawn (tracking + debug landmarks fine, but selecting a mask source shows nothing).",
      "file": "src/mask-renderer.cpp, data/effects/mask.effect",
      "root_cause": "Projective texcoord used tvarray[0].width = 3 (u/z, v/z, 1/z). The D3D11 backend only accepts texture-vertex widths of 2 or 4; width 3 makes gs_vertexbuffer_create return null, so render() hit 'if (!vb) return;' and skipped the mask. OpenGL (Linux dev) accepts width 3, which is why it worked there but not on the Windows .exe. Debug landmarks use the built-in SOLID effect (no custom vbuffer) so they kept drawing.",
      "fix": "Pad the projective texcoord to width 4: (u/z, v/z, 0, 1/z). mask-renderer.cpp writes 4 floats/vertex; mask.effect declares float4 uvq : TEXCOORD0 and divides uv = uvq.xy / uvq.w. Width 4 is valid on both D3D11 and GL.",
      "tags": [
        "windows",
        "d3d11",
        "obs-api",
        "graphics",
        "vertexbuffer",
        "shader",
        "cross-platform"
      ],
